⚙️ What is IOPS?
------------------------------
IOPS means Input/Output Operations Per Second.
It measures how fast a storage device (like SSD or disk) can read and write data.

💡 Why IOPS is Important
It shows performance of storage.
Higher IOPS = faster data access.
Important for databases, VMs, and applications that need quick response.

🕒 When to Use or Check IOPS
When you need high-speed storage (for example, running SQL Server, SAP, or virtual machines).
When you compare SSD vs HDD performance.
When you choose Azure Disk types (Standard HDD, Standard SSD, Premium SSD, Ultra Disk — each gives different IOPS).


